// ❌ Why this is broken:
// - Missing "/*" so GetObject will never work (object-level access requires the object ARN)
// - No s3:ListBucket permission, so listing objects always fails
// - Uses the bucket ARN for GetObject, which is incorrect
// - Looks correct at first glance, which is why this issue is common

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObject"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::my-demo-bucket"
    }
  ]
}
